	     <table class=mform  border=0 cellpadding=1 cellspacing=0 width=100%>
	     <form action=/cgi-bin/mrate.pl name=f104309003248540>
	     <tr><td id=headerrow colspan=2 class=mform valign=top><a name=/db/item.html?item=16749&mid=104309003248540>&nbsp;</a><a id=sj href=/db/item.html?item=16749&mid=104309003248540>Personal Horror Story about Ring</a> <a id=fs8 href=/db/item.html?item=16749&mid=104309003248540#post><img src=http://everquest.allakhazam.com/static/reply.gif border=0 alt="Reply..." height=16 width=16></a>
	     <br clear=all><small>Posted @ Mon, Jan 20th 2:42 PM 2003</small></td></tr>
	     <tr><td valign=top id=fs8 class=mform><span id=notbold>By:</span> <a href=poster.html?user=43695><span id=Sage>Argfeld</span></a><br><b><span id=Sage>Sage</span></b><br><span id=notbold>72 posts<br><span id=notbold>Score</span>: Default [1.88]</td><td valign=top class=mform width=100%><p>Let me tell you guys the story about what happened to my guild with this ring.<br><br>We had tried to kill AD a few times before and wiped out.&nbsp;&nbsp;Then, we worked out a strategy (sorry, it's top secret) that we hoped would work.  We tried it, and what do you know, it did work!  One of the loot items was some piece of crap shoulder item.  The other was the Ring of Nobility.  I put my name in the hat for it, not really expecting to get it, but hoping.  We had our temporary flags from killing AD, but had only a few of us had made it permanent by zoning into HoH.  Most of us were hanging around in lair waiting for the command to get flagged and/or hoping to get the ring.  While we were waiting for the loot decisions to be announced, we all started getting bad lag spikes.  Suddenly, I went LD.  I tried to log back on and discovered that the server was locked.  I discovered that my guild had set up a chat channel and that everyone on the raid had been kicked off the server.  Later, when the server came back online, we logged back on in the lair.  The server had been reset.  The golems were back up, but AD was not.  Our temporary flags were gone.  The loot was gone.  A GM eventually responded to our petitioning and told us we were out of luck.  Everyone had been rolled back a few minutes, and even those that had zoned and made their flags permanent discovered that they were no longer flagged.  One of my guildmates actually lost some items, although she was reimbursed for them.<br><br><br></p>&nbsp;<br></td></tr>
